stations.name: Myrtle Av (Elevated)
stations.description: Former BMT Myrtle Avenue elevated station, demolished when the elevated line was partially dismantled.

stations.name: Sedgwick Av
stations.description: Former IRT Jerome Avenue Line station between Burnside Avenue and 176th Street, closed for lack of ridership.

stations.name: Cortlandt St (original)
stations.description: Original IRT station destroyed in the September 11 attacks; later rebuilt and reopened in 2018 as WTC Cortlandt.

stations.name: City Hall (BMT)
stations.description: Former BMT Nassau Street terminal station, closed when the J/Z terminus moved to Broad Street.

stations.name: Canal St (BMT original)
stations.description: Former BMT Broadway/Nassau connection station, closed during the Manhattan Bridge reconfiguration.

stations.name: 116 St–Columbia University
stations.description: IRT Broadway–Seventh Avenue station at Columbia University in Morningside Heights.

stations.name: 79 St
stations.description: IRT Broadway–Seventh Avenue local station on the Upper West Side.

stations.name: 50 St
stations.description: Connected IRT Broadway and IND Eighth Avenue station complex at 50th Street.

stations.name: 18 St
stations.description: IRT Broadway–Seventh Avenue local station in Chelsea.

stations.name: 77 St
stations.description: IRT Lexington Avenue local station on the Upper East Side.

stations.name: Brooklyn Bridge–City Hall
stations.description: Southern terminus of the 6 train near City Hall and the Brooklyn Bridge in Lower Manhattan.
